data.text:
Scat and Tracks Drop In: Saturday, August 3, 10am-2pm

In this nature drop in we will discover some of the many animals that call Wisconsin home and the clues that they leave behind. Stop in anytime from 10am-2pm. Presented by Tom Lentz, Wisconsin Master Naturalist. Stop by anytime from 10am-2pm.

This FREE program is held at the Horicon Marsh Education and Visitor Center located at N7725 Highway 28, Horicon, WI, 53032. No registration required. Please direct questions to Liz Herzmann at Elizabeth.herzmann@wisconsin.gov or 920-387-7893.
